definition.value: A hydroxy-alkylglucosinolic acid that consists of 1-thio-beta-D-glucopyranose attached to a 3-hydroxy-3-methyl-N-(sulfooxy)pentanimidoyl group at the anomeric sulfur.
A hydroxy-alkylglucosinolic acid that consists of 1-thio-beta-D-glucopyranose attached to a 3-hydroxy-3-methyl-N-(sulfooxy)butanimidoyl group at the anomeric sulfur.
A glucosinolic acid with a indolylmethyl side-chain.
A indolylmethylglucosinolate that is the conjugate base of sulfoglucobrassicin.
A glucosinolic acid that consists of 1-thio-beta-D-glucopyranose attached to a 1-(methylsulfinyl)-5-[(sulfooxy)imino]pent-1-en-5-yl group at the anomeric sulfur.
A carbohydrazide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy groups of malonic acid with the hydrino groups of two molar equivalents of N-methylbenzenecarbothiohydrazide

An omega-hydroxy fatty acid ascaroside that is bhos#10 in which the hydroxy group at position 4 of the ascarylopyranose moiety has been has been converted to the corresponding 1H-indole-3-carboxylate ester. It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.

An omega-hydroxy fatty acid ascaroside that is bhos#16 in which the hydroxy group at position 4 of the ascarylopyranose moiety has been has been converted to the corresponding 1H-indole-3-carboxylate ester. It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.

An omega-hydroxy fatty acid ascaroside that is bhos#18 in which the hydroxy group at position 4 of the ascarylopyranose moiety has been has been converted to the corresponding 1H-indole-3-carboxylate ester. It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.

An omega-hydroxy fatty acid ascaroside that is bhos#20 in which the hydroxy group at position 4 of the ascarylopyranose moiety has been has been converted to the corresponding 1H-indole-3-carboxylate ester. It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.

An omega-hydroxy fatty acid ascaroside that is bhos#22 in which the hydroxy group at position 4 of the ascarylopyranose moiety has been has been converted to the corresponding 1H-indole-3-carboxylate ester. It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.

An omega-hydroxy fatty acid ascaroside that is bhos#24 in which the hydroxy group at position 4 of the ascarylopyranose moiety has been has been converted to the corresponding 1H-indole-3-carboxylate ester. It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.

An omega-hydroxy fatty acid ascaroside that is bhos#26 in which the hydroxy group at position 4 of the ascarylopyranose moiety has been has been converted to the corresponding 1H-indole-3-carboxylate ester. It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.
The copper coordination entity formed from elesclomol by coordination to copper via the thiocarbonyl and hydrazino groups.

A twelve-membered polypeptide comprising the sequence Tyr-Ile-Ile-Lys-Gly-Val-Phe-Trp-Asp-Pro-Ala-Cys. Corresponds to the P34165[22-33] fragment of mating hormone A-factor 1 from Saccharomyces cerevisiae (strain ATCC 204508/S288c).

A twelve-membered polypeptide comprising the sequence Tyr-Ile-Ile-Lys-Gly-Leu-Phe-Trp-Asp-Pro-Ala-Cys. Corresponds to the P34166[24-35] fragment of mating hormone A-factor 2 from Saccharomyces cerevisiae (strain ATCC 204508/S288c).
A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of (2E,4Z)-2-hydroxy-7-methyl-6-oxo-2,4-octadienoic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
A mixture of two twelve membered polypeptides having sequences of Tyr-Ile-Ile-Lys-Gly-Val-Phe-Trp-Asp-Pro-Ala-Cys and Tyr-Ile-Ile-Lys-Gly-Val-Phe-Trp-Asp-Pro-Ala-Cys.

A thirteen-membered polypeptide comprising the sequence Trp-His-Trp-Leu-Gln-Leu-Lys-Pro-Gly-Gln-Pro-Met-Tyr. Corresponds to the P01149[90-102] fragment of mating factor alpha-1 from Saccharomyces cerevisiae (strain ATCC 204508/S288c).
An oxo dicarboxylic acid that is 3-carboxy-6-oxoocta-2,4-dienoic acid carrying additional hydroxy and methyl substituents at positions 2 and 7 respectively.
A member of the class of quinolines that is 2-methoixyquinoline carrying additional 4-chlorobenzyl and (4-carboxamidinopiperidin-1-yl)methyl substituents at positions 3 and 6 respectively.
A terpene lactone that is obtained from Codinea simplex and acts as an inhibitor of glycerophosphoinositol biosynthesis.
A pathway inhibitor that disrupts the synthesis of glycerophosphoinositol
Any inorganic anion with a valency of three.
Any inorganic anion with a valency of two.
Any inorganic anion with a valency of one.
A sesquiterpene lactone and active principle of Feverfew (Tanacetum parthenium).
A non-proteinogenic L-alpha-amino acid that is L-alanine in which the methyl group is replaced by a (2R,5S)-5-methyl-2,5-dihydrofuran-2-yl moiety.
A thiinoindole that is 3,5-dihydro-2H-thiino[4,3,2-cd]indole which is substituted at positions 2 and 3 by carboxy and methyl groups, respectively (the 2R,3S diastereoisomer).
An EC 6.1.1.* (ligases forming aminoacyl tRNA and related compounds) inhibitor that interferes with the action of any tryptophan--tRNA ligase (EC 6.1.1.2).
Any organic heterotricyclic compound that consists of a thiopyran ring fused to an indole.
A member of the class of 1,3-oxazoles that is 1,3-oxazol-4(5H)-one which is substituted at the 2 and 5-pro-S positions by methylamino and [(1R)-1-(1H-indol-3-yl)ethyl] groups, respectively.
A mixture resulting from extraction of the bark (also leaves) of any member of the genus Salix. The main active ingredient is salicin.

A carbotricyclic compound and sesquiterpenoid tertiary alcohol that is tricyclo[5.3.1.0(3,8)]undecan-3-ol which is substituted at positions 2, 2, 6 and 8 by methyl groups (the 1R,3R,6S,7S,8S-diastereoisomer).
An organic sulfate salt containing equimolar amounts of vincristine(2+) and sulfate. Used for the treatment of a variety of cancers.
